<section xmlns="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook" xml:id="DisableOddjobd" version="5.0">
 <title xml:id="SysMgmtServices">Disable Oddjobd</title>
 <para>
  The oddjob daemon provides some additional ability to execute actions
  via the D-Bus interface, but it is recommended that the service be
  disabled unless required.
 </para>
 <informaltable frame="all" cellspacing="2" cellpadding="2">
  <tgroup cols="3">
   <colspec colname="c1" colwidth="0.8*" align="left"/>
   <colspec colname="c2" colwidth="0.5*"/>
   <colspec colname="c3" colwidth="0.5*"/>
   <thead>
    <row>
     <entry>Operating Systems</entry>
     <entry>Packages</entry>
     <entry>Service Names</entry>
    </row>
   </thead>
   <tbody valign="middle">
    <row>
     <entry>Fedora 10, 11, 12, and 13</entry>
     <entry namest="c2" nameend="c3"><emphasis>Operating System Not Applicable</emphasis></entry>
    </row>
    <row>
     <entry>Red Hat Enterprise Linux 4</entry>
     <entry morerows="2">oddjob</entry>
     <entry morerows="2">oddjobd</entry>
    </row>
    <row>
     <entry>Red Hat Enterprise Linux 5</entry>
    </row>
    <row>
     <entry>Red Hat Enterprise Linux 6</entry>
    </row>
    <row>
     <entry>SUSE 10 and 11</entry>
     <entry morerows="1" namest="c2" nameend="c3"><emphasis>Operating System Not Applicable</emphasis></entry>
    </row>
    <row>
     <entry>Solaris 10</entry>
    </row>
   </tbody>
  </tgroup>
 </informaltable>
 <simplesect xml:id="DisableOddjobd-compliancy">
  <title>Compliancy</title>
